<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-120-004 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 941 360</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  July 1991 v2 n7 p317(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Three months, no problem. (Durability Test) (Hardware Review)(Blue Star Computers' 386SX Cache microcomputer) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lockwood, Russ.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Blue Star Computers' $2,199 386SX Cache is a 20-MHx Intel80386SX-based microcomputer that offers reliability and good valuefor the money.andP;  Priced in the middle of the range for this type ofsystem, the product handles all workloads without a hitch,including Microsoft Windows 3.0 applications.andP;  The system usesintegrated motherboards and a 64Kbyte memory cache to speedoperations and offers first rate performance.andP;  The companyprovides excellent 24-hour technical support and overnight partsshipment service.andP;  The 386SX Cache microcomputer is a solidmachine that offers reliable performance.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Blue Star Computers (Products).andO;Product:   Blue Star 386SX Cache (Microcomputer).andO;Topic:     EvaluationMicrocomputers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>After three months of virtual non-stop use, the Blue Star 386SX Cachecontinues to handle everything I can throw on its hard drive without aproblem.andP;  Windows applications, word processors, spreadsheets, enetertainmentsoftware--you name it, the 386SX Cache runs it.andM;I'm harping on the software compatibility issue because Blue Star relies on aMicroid Research (MR) BIOS, not exactly one of the best-known BIOSmanufacturers.andP;  Yet the BIOS never flinched while running program afterprogram.andP;  I haven't taken advantage of the password protection function ofthe BIOS, but it's nice to know I can--and that's one reason why Blue Starwent with an Mr rather than with an AMI BIOS.andP;  Note that Blue Star willsubstitute an AMI BIOS FOR THE MR BIOS at no charge.andP;  I cannot vouch fornetworking software, since I used this unit as a standalone desktop computer.andO;But I'd expect no problems.andM;The company dropped its optional TRW service, and now relies exclusively onovernight parts shipment and 24-hour technical support.andP;  Because of thetechnicians' past excellence and the machine's reliable service, I anticipateresponsive and reliable service for a long time to come.andP;  At one point, Igave the technical support department a quick call to see if time haddiminished its effectiveness.andP;  Everyone was still knowledgeable and eager.andM;I was also pleased to discover that the price had dropped $200 for a loadedsystem, from $2,399 to $2,199, over three months.andP;  The 386SX Cache is not theleast expensive 20MHz cached SX-based system around, but it's right in themiddle of the price range.andM;Blue Star leapt ahead in 20MHz SX system design, using integratedmotherboards and a 64K RAM cache with its 386SX Cache.andP;  First-rateperformance, backed by excellent and responsive technical support, shows thata small company can score early and score big.andO;</TEXT></DOC>